Description: This nonfiction book examines the impact of algorithms and big data on various aspects of society, such as education, employment, and criminal justice. It argues that these technologies can often perpetuate biases and inequalities, and proposes ways to create more ethical and transparent systems.

Tittle: Web Design with HTML, CSS, JavaScript and jQuery Set
Author: Jon Duckett
Description: This instructional book is a comprehensive guide to web design, covering the basics of HTML, CSS, and JavaScript, as well as more advanced topics such as responsive design and jQuery. It includes numerous examples and exercises to help readers build their skills.

Author: Randall Munroe
Description: This nonfiction book answers absurd hypothetical questions using scientific principles and humor. The author, a former NASA roboticist and the creator of the webcomic xkcd, explores topics such as what would happen if you tried to hit a baseball pitched at 90 percent the speed of light, or if everyone on Earth jumped at the same time.

Author: Paul Kalanithi
Description: This memoir chronicles the life and death of Paul Kalanithi, a neurosurgeon who was diagnosed with terminal lung cancer at the age of 36. It reflects on the meaning of life and death, and the pursuit of a meaningful existence.

Author: Peter Mayle
Description: This book is a humorous and informative guide to reproduction, aimed at children and young adults. It covers the basics of human anatomy, sex, and childbirth in a lighthearted and accessible way, using illustrations and simple language.

Author: Judy Horacek
Description: This children's book is a playful and colorful exploration of different types of sheep, each with its own personality and characteristics. The story follows a group of sheep as they search for a missing green sheep, with lively illustrations and rhyming text.

Author: Spencer Johnson
Description: This self-help book uses a fictional story to illustrate the importance of adapting to change and taking personal responsibility for one's own success. It follows the journey of four characters who must navigate a maze to find cheese, with each character representing a different approach to dealing with change.

Author: R. J. Palacio
Description: This young adult novel tells the story of August Pullman, a boy with facial differences who is starting fifth grade in a mainstream school for the first time. The book explores themes of bullying, empathy, and acceptance, as August navigates the challenges of making friends and fitting in.

Author: Blizzard
Description: It is written by BLIZZARD ENTERTAINMENT and is the first of the three books in the Chronicle series which attempts to codify, tighten up and clarify the history of Warcraft. The book reveals untold stories about the birth of the cosmos, the rise of ancient empires, and the forces that shaped Azeroth

Author: Keri Smith
Description: This book is an interactive journal that encourages readers to engage in creative and unconventional ways of self-expression. It includes prompts and exercises that challenge traditional notions of journaling.

Author: Leslie Kaminoff
Description: It provides detailed anatomical illustrations of yoga poses and the muscles used during each pose. The book is divided into five parts: the skeletal system, the muscular system, breathing, the nervous system, and the anatomy of the yoga poses.
